CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 30, 1944, pg. 11, reads: "The 1944 Crop of Courier Babies had males predominating, which bodes well for the future debbies. This handsome array of talent and charm and beauty all have Courier backgrounds, which may influence the future of the youngsters.  So, for a Christmas and New Year's gift to you....bottom row...Ira Vann Harris, son of Mr. and Mrs. Charles (Teenie) Harris (Courier staff photographer)... - Courier photos by Harris and Sockwell."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of baby Ira Vann Harris, son of Charles "Teenie" Harris, wearing scalloped edge socks, seated in high chair, in domestic interior with door in background, possibly in Harris home at 7604 Mulford Street, Homewood
